What chemistry teaches your framework

Chemistry forces a correction that is very valuable:

meaning is not free-floating; it is constrained by compatibility

In chemistry, not every atom can do everything. Valence, charge, geometry, orbital compatibility, solvent context, temperature, and pressure all matter.

